[3] OIE notification
Date: Fri, 2 Jan 2015
Source: OIE, WAHID weekly disease information 2015; 28(02) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapEventSummary&reportid=16869


Low pathogenic avian influenza (poultry), Hong Kong (SAR-PRC)
-------------------------------------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 2 Jan 2015 from Dr Thomas Sit, Chief Veterinary Officer / Assistant Director (Inspection & Quarantine), Agriculture, Fisheries and Conservation Department, Hong Kong Special Administrative Region Government, Hong Kong , Hong Kong (SAR - PRC)

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 30 Dec 2014
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 30 Dec 2014
Report date: 02 Jan 2015
Date submitted to OIE: 2 Jan 2015
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 28 Apr 2014
Manifestation of disease: sub-clinical infection
Causal agent: Low pathogenic avian influenza virus
Serotype: H7N9
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks (1)
Outbreak 1: 4 Hing Wah Street, Cheung Sha Wan, Hong Kong
Date of start of the outbreak: 30 Dec 2014
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: not applicable
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Birds / 18 962 / 1 / 0 / 18 962 / 0
Affected population: an imported consignment of live chickens was tested positive for low pathogenic avian influenza H7N9 virus during regular surveillance on 30 Dec 2014.

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: legal movement of animals
Epidemiological comments: an intensive surveillance system is in place for all imported poultry, wild bird, local poultry farms, poultry markets, and pet bird shops. An imported consignment containing 1200 chickens was tested positive for low pathogenic avian influenza virus (H7N9) during the routine surveillance programme. A total of 18 962 poultry, including 11 800 chickens, 3140 silky chickens, 1025 chukars, and 2997 pigeons were culled on 31 Dec 2014. Importation of live poultry is banned for 21 days.

Control measures
Measures applied: stamping out, quarantine, movement control inside the country, screening, zoning, disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s), no vaccination, no treatment of affected animals.
Measures to be applied: no other measures:

Diagnostic test results
a. Laboratory name and type: Tai Lung Veterinary Laboratory, Agriculture, Fisheries and Conservation Department (national laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
1. Birds / haemagglutination inhibition test (HIT) / 30 Dec 2014 / Positive
2. Birds / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 30 Dec 2014 / Positive
3. Birds / virus isolation / Pending
b. Centre of Influenza Research, School of Public Health, Li Ka Shing Faculty of Medicine, The University of Hong Kong (regional reference laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Birds / gene sequencing / Pending

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

